    .{
        .name = "runtime",
        .path = "src/services/runtime/mod.zig",
        .description = "Runtime Module - Always-on Core Infrastructure\n\nThis module provides the foundational runtime infrastructure that is always\navailable regardless of which features are enabled. It includes:\n\n- Task scheduling and execution engine\n- Concurrency primitives (futures, task groups, cancellation)\n- Memory management utilities\n\n## Module Organization\n\n```\nruntime/\n\xe2\x94\x9c\xe2\x94\x80\xe2\x94\x80 mod.zig          # This file - unified entry point\n\xe2\x94\x9c\xe2\x94\x80\xe2\x94\x80 engine/          # Task execution engine\n\xe2\x94\x9c\xe2\x94\x80\xe2\x94\x80 scheduling/      # Futures, cancellation, task groups\n\xe2\x94\x9c\xe2\x94\x80\xe2\x94\x80 concurrency/     # Lock-free data structures\n\xe2\x94\x94\xe2\x94\x80\xe2\x94\x80 memory/          # Memory pools and allocators\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```zig\nconst runtime = @import(\"runtime\");\n\n// Create runtime context\nvar ctx = try runtime.Context.init(allocator);\ndefer ctx.deinit();\n\n// Use task groups for parallel work\nvar group = try ctx.createTaskGroup(.{});\ndefer group.deinit();\n```",
        .category = "Compute & Runtime",
        .build_flag = "always-on",
        .symbols = .{
